    "created_at": "2016-03-06T07:17:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-06T07:17:53Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz I've been looking into this issue further, and I believe it's rooted deeper in the design of electron's browser-side state storage.  The way that it is implemented now there is a lot of dependency on the main process for simple state queries. Instead the renderer process should cache and mirror the state of the main process, updating it via asynchronous messaging.\n\nI'm interested in hearing your thoughts on this, and would be open to implementing the changes.\n"
  },
